WEBVTT

00:01.501 --> 00:03.803
♪♪

00:04.671 --> 00:06.506
[ Saweetie's "Best Friend"
plays ]

00:06.573 --> 00:09.009
♪ That my best friend,
she a real bad... ♪

00:09.075 --> 00:11.578
♪ Got her own money
she don't need no drinks ♪

00:11.678 --> 00:14.347
♪ Now she twerkin', she throw it
out and come back in ♪

00:14.414 --> 00:16.049
Wait, guys,
here's a debate topic.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.318
Is it better to buy
expensive furniture

00:18.385 --> 00:19.853
that's already assembled

00:19.919 --> 00:22.422
or cheap stuff that you have to
put together yourself?

00:22.522 --> 00:25.425
Keep in mind, I already
bought the cheap stuff.

00:25.525 --> 00:26.393
[ Chuckles ]

00:26.493 --> 00:28.395
[<i> Bells chime</i> ]

00:31.865 --> 00:33.566
Morning, Meadows Creek High!

00:33.666 --> 00:36.503
It's time for
your Escalante Minute.

00:36.569 --> 00:38.038
<i>That's just a title,</i>

00:38.104 --> 00:39.439
<i>'cause it's gonna be</i>
<i>a lot longer than that.</i>

00:39.539 --> 00:40.940
Come on.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.842
-Why?!
-Okay, hey, hey, come on.

00:42.909 --> 00:45.011
At least he's not doing
the cheesy theme song.

00:45.078 --> 00:46.246
Wait for it.

00:46.346 --> 00:49.382
♪ It's the Escalante Minute ♪

00:49.449 --> 00:53.219
♪ The best minute
of your month ♪

00:54.387 --> 00:55.588
Wow.

00:55.688 --> 00:57.757
Those vocal coaches
are really paying off.

00:57.857 --> 01:00.760
Okay, first up,
exciting poetry news.

01:00.860 --> 01:02.295
I've picked a winner
for this year's

01:02.395 --> 01:05.932
Elliot Escalante Exceptional
Excellence in Poetry,

01:06.032 --> 01:08.435
AKA The EEEEP.

01:08.535 --> 01:09.803
<i>That's my poetry contest,</i>

01:09.903 --> 01:12.472
for those of you
living under a rock.

01:12.572 --> 01:15.141
Okay.
And this year's winner is...

01:15.241 --> 01:18.645
[<i> Drumroll plays</i> ]

01:18.745 --> 01:20.313
<i>...Sarah Maris!</i>

01:20.413 --> 01:21.548
[<i> Applause</i> ]

01:21.614 --> 01:22.982
I think I've died
and gone to Hell.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.484
Please don't read it!

01:24.584 --> 01:25.752
And now I'm gonna read it.

01:25.819 --> 01:27.654
Oh, my...

01:27.754 --> 01:30.056
<i>"My heart longs</i>
<i>to never lose you.</i>

01:30.123 --> 01:32.492
I promise to always choose you.

01:32.592 --> 01:34.327
And when the waters clear,

01:34.427 --> 01:36.796
<i>it will always be you</i>
<i>I hold dear.</i>

01:36.896 --> 01:38.264
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God,

01:38.331 --> 01:39.599
oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God.

01:39.666 --> 01:41.167
Oh, my God, Oh, my God.

01:41.267 --> 01:42.769
[ Door closes ]

01:42.836 --> 01:45.138
Shoot. You guys, do you think
I should go after her?

01:45.238 --> 01:49.275
Would you want you
to go after you?

01:49.342 --> 01:51.344
Point taken.

01:51.444 --> 01:53.780
Terrell,
you are the man.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.949
I mean, that is
obviously about you.

01:56.015 --> 01:57.350
Oh, my God.

01:57.450 --> 01:58.852
It is my dream
to be the subject

01:58.952 --> 02:00.320
of a love poem...

02:00.420 --> 02:01.688
that I didn't write.

02:02.956 --> 02:05.692
Bro, I didn't know y'all
were actually that serious.

02:05.792 --> 02:07.193
I didn't either.

02:07.293 --> 02:09.128
I mean, and I thought Sarah
was normally really private.

02:09.195 --> 02:10.864
Well, Emily Dickinson
was a shut-in,

02:10.964 --> 02:12.832
and she was an amazing poet...

02:12.932 --> 02:14.334
until she drowned
in that river.

02:14.434 --> 02:16.803
Wait, no.
That was Virginia Woolf.

02:16.870 --> 02:19.272
Or, no, that was the one
that put her head in the oven.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.876
Wow. God,
so many troubled ladies.

02:22.976 --> 02:25.378
Again, that poem
is by Sarah Maris.

02:25.478 --> 02:27.780
So if you see Sarah Maris
in the hallway,

02:27.847 --> 02:29.883
make sure to tell her
how much you love it.

02:29.983 --> 02:31.317
Again -- Sarah?

02:33.019 --> 02:34.320
Where'd you get the keys?

02:34.387 --> 02:35.321
[ Bag thuds ]

02:35.388 --> 02:37.290
Your minute is done.

02:37.357 --> 02:38.391
No, don't touch that.

02:38.491 --> 02:40.560
<i>No!</i>
<i>That's my lucky mic, dude!</i>

02:40.660 --> 02:42.228
<i>Sarah, don't</i>
<i>throw those pencils.</i>

02:42.328 --> 02:44.164
<i>Not the face!</i>

02:44.230 --> 02:45.665
[ Clears throat ]

02:46.633 --> 02:48.201
Back to my furniture.

02:49.169 --> 02:50.203
♪♪

02:50.303 --> 02:52.205
♪ Oh-oh-oh, oh, oh-oh, oh ♪

02:52.305 --> 02:54.340
♪ Oh-oh-oh, oh, oh ♪

02:54.407 --> 02:56.242
♪ Oh-oh-oh, oh, oh-oh, oh ♪

02:56.342 --> 02:58.011
♪ Oh-oh-oh, oh ♪

02:58.077 --> 03:00.547
[ Whistle blows ]

03:00.647 --> 03:01.981
♪♪

03:02.048 --> 03:04.817
[ Cellphone chiming ]

03:06.186 --> 03:08.421
Guys, we're standing
right next to each other.

03:10.323 --> 03:12.225
Is this still about
the Dave & Buster's incident

03:12.325 --> 03:13.560
from<i> last</i> weekend?

03:13.660 --> 03:16.396
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:16.496 --> 03:17.830
[ Sighs ]

03:17.897 --> 03:20.600
Okay, look, you guys always
do this when you fight.

03:20.700 --> 03:22.869
Why can't we just
talk about it IRL?

03:22.936 --> 03:24.604
Because we're all addicted
to our phones.

03:24.704 --> 03:27.240
Exactly.
Who's up for a challenge?

03:27.340 --> 03:29.542
Oh, is it to see who can go
to the best college,

03:29.609 --> 03:31.844
make the most money,
and pay the least taxes?

03:32.845 --> 03:36.449
No, it's to see who can go
the longest without their phone.

03:36.549 --> 03:38.952
That's fine. I'll just play
that little game by myself.

03:39.886 --> 03:41.921
So, uh, what are the stakes
of this phone thing?

03:42.021 --> 03:44.357
Losers buy the winner coffee
for a week.

03:44.424 --> 03:46.793
Okay. In.
This is gonna be easy.

03:46.893 --> 03:49.696
Good luck, suckers.
<i>You</i> are gonna need it.

03:50.597 --> 03:52.632
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:55.368 --> 03:57.070
No, I can't do it.

03:57.136 --> 03:59.973
Oh, I missed you so much.

04:01.574 --> 04:03.376
Have fun
with your dumb contest.

04:03.443 --> 04:05.912
♪♪

04:05.979 --> 04:07.614
Nope, too old.

04:07.714 --> 04:09.382
Nope, too young.

04:09.449 --> 04:10.950
Nope, two kids.

04:11.050 --> 04:13.086
[ Sighs ]
Alicia, I screwed up,

04:13.152 --> 04:14.153
and I really need
your help.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.389
Nope, too needy.

04:16.456 --> 04:18.825
Do not swipe left
on my problems.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.159
I am in the middle
of a crisis.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.427
Okay, I'm sorry.
I didn't know.

04:21.494 --> 04:23.096
But, wait.
Before we get into it,

04:23.162 --> 04:25.498
does Dante look like he could
put together a bookshelf?

04:25.598 --> 04:27.567
You looking for a boyfriend
or a TaskRabbit?

04:27.634 --> 04:28.835
Why can't it be both?

04:28.935 --> 04:30.470
Okay, look.

04:30.570 --> 04:33.239
I keep telling Sarah I was just
trying to celebrate her talents,

04:33.306 --> 04:37.844
but all she does is,
"La la la la, la la la la, la!"

04:37.944 --> 04:39.512
It's so damn effective.

04:40.513 --> 04:41.914
Why are you smiling
at me?

04:41.981 --> 04:44.851
'Cause you, my friend,
pulled an Alicia.

04:44.951 --> 04:47.620
You got overenthusiastic
about helping a student,

04:47.687 --> 04:49.489
completely disregarded
personal boundaries,

04:49.589 --> 04:50.757
and it blew up in your face.

04:50.823 --> 04:52.825
Oh, my God.

04:52.925 --> 04:54.794
I went<i> full</i> Alicia.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.363
It is really stressful.

04:57.463 --> 04:58.698
This is how you live?

04:58.798 --> 05:01.267
Eh, you get used to it.

05:01.334 --> 05:02.869
But, you know, looking at it
from this side,

05:02.969 --> 05:04.671
I am feeling so at peace.

05:05.772 --> 05:07.206
Is this how<i> you</i> live?

05:07.307 --> 05:09.208
Before now!

05:09.309 --> 05:10.877
Come on.
You don't have any advice?

05:10.977 --> 05:12.645
If I got involved
in your situation,

05:12.712 --> 05:13.880
that would be pulling
an Alicia.

05:13.980 --> 05:15.848
But you are Alicia.

05:15.948 --> 05:17.784
Today, I'm the girl
grading papers,

05:17.850 --> 05:19.519
eating other people's
leftovers,

05:19.619 --> 05:21.220
and bingeing
this train wreck.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.189
Listen, I'm not taking "no"
for an answer.

05:24.490 --> 05:27.393
La, la, la, la, la, la, la, la,
la, la, la, la, la, la, la, la!

05:27.493 --> 05:31.064
But seriously --

05:32.332 --> 05:34.701
Okay, listen, I know
you're totally embarrassed,

05:34.801 --> 05:36.002
but I can relate.

05:36.069 --> 05:37.970
You know, once, when I --

05:38.037 --> 05:40.139
my poem being read
over the PA

05:40.206 --> 05:41.908
to the time you had a leaf
stuck in your hair.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.676
On picture day.

05:45.845 --> 05:46.846
Here.

05:46.913 --> 05:48.247
Why are you bringing us
two coffees?

05:48.348 --> 05:49.849
[ Gasps ]
Ooh, did you --

05:49.916 --> 05:51.551
Yep. I caved.

05:51.651 --> 05:53.152
Timothée Chalamet went live.

05:53.219 --> 05:55.888
I really wasn't thinking
when I made this bet.

05:57.490 --> 05:59.992
And then there were two.

06:00.059 --> 06:02.095
Question --
How do you guys know

06:02.195 --> 06:03.596
the other isn't looking
at their phone?

06:03.696 --> 06:05.598
I know I can be trusted.

06:05.698 --> 06:08.534
Three words --
Dave & Buster's.

06:09.502 --> 06:12.372
If you can cheat there,
you can cheat anywhere.

06:12.438 --> 06:15.174
Two words -- up yours.

06:16.042 --> 06:17.243
Well, since I'm out,

06:17.343 --> 06:18.778
I guess I can hold on
to your phones.

06:18.878 --> 06:20.947
Thank you, but I think
you're underestimating us.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.949
Oh, my God, did you see
the pic I just sent

06:23.049 --> 06:25.685
of a kitty
sleeping with a squirrel?

06:25.752 --> 06:28.087
Oh, my God, they're tucked into
a tiny little bed.

06:28.187 --> 06:29.422
Take 'em.

06:31.924 --> 06:34.227
Hey. Hey, great job
ending the Escalante Minute

06:34.293 --> 06:35.795
before he got
to the closing theme song.

06:35.895 --> 06:38.030
Well,
I had to pull the plug.

06:38.097 --> 06:39.232
Literally.

06:39.298 --> 06:41.100
[ Chuckles ]

06:41.200 --> 06:43.936
Don't be.
It was an awesome poem.

06:44.036 --> 06:45.638
Probably because you had
a great muse.

06:45.738 --> 06:46.606
[ Chuckles ]

06:46.706 --> 06:47.807
It was me.
I'm the muse.

06:47.907 --> 06:50.410
I was following.

06:50.476 --> 06:52.311
Look, the poem
was unexpected

06:52.412 --> 06:54.147
but really cool.

06:55.381 --> 06:56.716
Okay.
You know, I'm gonna go...

06:56.783 --> 06:59.318
Both: Let the air out
of Mr. Escalante's tires.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.386
Am I becoming predictable?

07:00.453 --> 07:01.788
Nah,
it's your signature move.

07:02.655 --> 07:04.056
I'll see you.

07:07.126 --> 07:09.462
What are you doing
in here?

07:09.562 --> 07:12.398
I'm a teacher
in the teachers' lounge.

07:12.465 --> 07:13.900
What are<i> you</i> doing
in here?

07:13.966 --> 07:15.301
My mom's the principal.

07:15.401 --> 07:17.003
I can go anywhere I want.

07:18.004 --> 07:20.339
Because I copied the keys.

07:20.440 --> 07:21.607
Sarah!

07:22.975 --> 07:24.944
Are any of those
for the vending machine?

07:25.011 --> 07:26.679
You know, today has been
so frustrating.

07:26.779 --> 07:27.914
Tell me about it.

07:27.980 --> 07:29.015
You know, I had
all this IKEA furniture

07:29.115 --> 07:30.416
delivered to my apartment,

07:30.483 --> 07:31.818
and there was no one
to help me set it up.

07:31.918 --> 07:33.119
You know, that is
an interesting thing

07:33.186 --> 07:35.087
that I do not care
anything about.

07:37.156 --> 07:40.860
No nosy follow-up
after I tell you I'm frustrated?

07:40.960 --> 07:42.028
It's refreshing.

07:42.128 --> 07:43.529
Thank you for noticing.

07:43.629 --> 07:46.432
Well, the new Alicia is staying
out of everybody's business.

07:46.499 --> 07:48.501
Awesome. You know, I'm glad
we're on the same page.

07:49.335 --> 07:50.670
Is it because you weren't ready
for Terrell

07:50.770 --> 07:51.971
to know how you really feel?

07:52.038 --> 07:54.540
[ Scoffs ]
Is something I<i> would</i> say

07:54.640 --> 07:56.209
if I was gonna get
involved.

07:56.309 --> 08:00.046
God, why does everybody assume
they know what the poem's about?

08:00.146 --> 08:02.181
Holy plot twist.

08:02.281 --> 08:04.050
It's not about Terrell,
is it?

08:05.117 --> 08:06.385
But, wait,
I just saw you guys out there,

08:06.486 --> 08:08.621
like, laughing and vibing.

08:08.688 --> 08:10.690
You were faking it.
Of course.

08:10.790 --> 08:12.458
But, wait.
Why not just tell him?

08:13.493 --> 08:15.661
Right.
'Cause he's such a good guy,

08:15.728 --> 08:16.996
you don't want to hurt
his feelings.

08:17.063 --> 08:18.397
I get it, girl.

08:19.665 --> 08:20.967
Don't you feel
so much better

08:21.033 --> 08:22.835
now that you got all of that
off your chest?

08:22.902 --> 08:24.704
Considering I didn't know
it was there?

08:25.671 --> 08:27.573
Definitely.

08:27.673 --> 08:29.742
He's gonna be so upset
when he finds out.

08:29.842 --> 08:33.412
Yeah, but he's gonna be
heartbroken if you lead him on.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.715
Being real
is the kinder thing to do.

08:35.815 --> 08:37.250
I don't know
if I can do that to him.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.585
No, it's like waxing --
you just gotta rip it off,

08:39.685 --> 08:41.020
or the pain's gonna linger.

08:41.087 --> 08:42.922
I think you need to pay more
for waxing.

08:44.357 --> 08:45.892
I'm gonna butt out.

08:45.992 --> 08:47.994
No, you're right.

08:48.060 --> 08:50.096
I just need to tell him
in my own way.

08:50.196 --> 08:52.331
Okay. And I am glad that
you came to that conclusion

08:52.398 --> 08:54.267
all on your own
without my involvement.

08:54.367 --> 08:55.735
Great.
Now can I have some privacy?

08:55.835 --> 08:57.770
I can't leave a student
in here unsupervised.

08:58.771 --> 09:00.006
Later.

09:00.072 --> 09:02.942
♪♪

09:03.042 --> 09:04.544
You know, Miles,
I gotta tell you,

09:04.610 --> 09:06.078
now that I'm off my phone,

09:06.178 --> 09:10.383
I feel so --
so clear-headed and calm.

09:10.449 --> 09:11.450
Really?

09:11.551 --> 09:13.052
'Cause you look
pale and sweaty.

09:13.119 --> 09:15.454
'Cause I skipped
all the way here.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.456
[ Chuckles ]
That's just something I do now.

09:17.557 --> 09:20.259
You -- You -- You'd get it
if you were off the grid.

09:22.461 --> 09:25.097
Oh, excuse me.
I didn't order scones.

09:25.197 --> 09:26.699
No, no, no, no,
no, no!

09:26.766 --> 09:31.537
<i>That</i> is just a gift
for giving me my life back.

09:31.604 --> 09:35.775
The light in me
sees the light in you.

09:38.110 --> 09:40.546
Your phone's
not in my backpack.

09:40.613 --> 09:41.981
Damn it! Okay.

09:42.081 --> 09:43.816
Look, look, look.

09:43.916 --> 09:45.318
Just give me
one little peek, right?

09:45.418 --> 09:47.420
Just to bring me down
a little bit.

09:47.486 --> 09:50.089
Is he caving?

09:50.156 --> 09:51.724
No.

09:51.791 --> 09:53.392
Now please be gone.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.998
Did he really think he
could distract me that easily?

09:59.098 --> 10:00.666
I know.
It's so pathetic.

10:00.766 --> 10:02.668
It's like he doesn't
even give you any credit.

10:02.768 --> 10:05.171
Oh, also, by the way,
I was just outside earlier.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.639
Griffin was looking
for you.

10:06.739 --> 10:07.773
That's really funny,

10:07.840 --> 10:09.275
'cause he's in Chicago
with family.

10:09.342 --> 10:10.910
And, no, your phone's
not in my backpack.

10:10.977 --> 10:12.678
Damn it.

10:12.778 --> 10:13.946
Ha!

10:14.013 --> 10:15.581
Uh, who's pathetic now?

10:15.648 --> 10:16.749
This girl.

10:18.184 --> 10:20.286
You two don't realize it,
but you have way more in common

10:20.353 --> 10:21.287
than you think you do.

10:21.354 --> 10:22.488
Gross.

10:22.588 --> 10:33.866
♪♪

10:33.966 --> 10:35.968
Welp,
someone's getting fired.

10:36.035 --> 10:38.137
Not if you pretend
you didn't see me.

10:38.204 --> 10:39.639
Sarah won't accept
my apology

10:39.705 --> 10:41.107
even though
I just gave her this.

10:41.173 --> 10:43.342
You made her another
homemade wizard wand?

10:43.442 --> 10:46.178
It was a Mylar balloon that said
"You're #1."

10:46.278 --> 10:47.480
She friggin' popped it.

10:48.314 --> 10:49.882
It was nice
working with you.

10:49.982 --> 10:52.385
I'm gonna miss your...

10:52.485 --> 10:54.453
faux snake boots.

10:54.520 --> 10:55.855
Hey.

10:55.955 --> 10:56.989
Typical Alicia move.

10:57.056 --> 10:58.491
You are spiraling.

10:58.557 --> 11:00.192
And you know what makes Alicia
feel better?

11:00.292 --> 11:01.727
Hmm?

11:01.827 --> 11:03.362
Come on, eat it, relax.
You're not gonna get fired.

11:03.462 --> 11:04.830
Sarah would never do that.

11:04.897 --> 11:06.565
Well, how do you know that?
Did you talk to her?

11:06.666 --> 11:08.034
You got involved?

11:08.134 --> 11:11.003
And there go your
chocolate privileges.

11:11.070 --> 11:13.472
For the record,
I am so not involved.

11:13.539 --> 11:17.043
♪♪

11:17.143 --> 11:19.578
Sarah's clearly into me
based on that poem,

11:19.679 --> 11:20.880
but, you know, in person,

11:20.980 --> 11:22.915
her actions just don't
match her words.

11:23.015 --> 11:25.051
Makayla: She's probably upset
you haven't done

11:25.151 --> 11:26.252
something equally romantic.

11:26.352 --> 11:28.087
Well, I was thinking
about buying her

11:28.187 --> 11:29.422
her favorite
swim goggles.

11:29.522 --> 11:31.424
Yeah, do not do that.

11:31.524 --> 11:33.259
Come on.
That poem was amazing.

11:33.359 --> 11:35.428
You really need to
step it up, bro.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.863
You should buy her
this bracelet, okay?

11:37.930 --> 11:40.766
It's ethically sourced,
so twice the price.

11:40.866 --> 11:43.502
Oh, my God, yeah,
she would love that.

11:43.569 --> 11:46.338
And I'm her best friend,
so I can borrow it from her.

11:46.405 --> 11:47.673
I guess I gotta do it.

11:47.740 --> 11:49.775
It's gonna cost
my entire summer savings.

11:49.875 --> 11:51.677
No, it's not!

11:51.744 --> 11:53.245
I mean, girls don't like

11:53.345 --> 11:55.181
expensive, lavish,
surprise gifts.

11:55.247 --> 11:56.248
Yuck.

11:56.348 --> 11:57.616
If you really
wanna win her heart,

11:57.717 --> 11:59.585
you should ask her to...

11:59.685 --> 12:01.287
sit under a tree
with you.

12:02.421 --> 12:05.257
Oh, did a little birdie
follow you to work, too?

12:05.357 --> 12:07.860
Okay, well, Sarah
does love to be outside,

12:07.927 --> 12:09.695
so maybe I'll go
with that idea.

12:09.762 --> 12:11.731
Wise decision.

12:11.797 --> 12:12.865
Thanks, Ms. G.

12:12.932 --> 12:14.033
Uh-huh.

12:15.267 --> 12:16.969
Bye-ee!

12:17.069 --> 12:19.205
Doesn't she seem
weirder than normal?

12:19.271 --> 12:20.940
No.

12:21.040 --> 12:25.911
♪♪

12:25.978 --> 12:27.279
Bro, your move.

12:27.379 --> 12:28.748
Don't rush me.

12:30.149 --> 12:32.151
Great.
Another tie.

12:32.251 --> 12:36.055
So I guess this is what
people did before phones.

12:36.122 --> 12:36.989
Yeah.

12:37.089 --> 12:38.791
But it, uh, made us talk

12:38.891 --> 12:42.795
and put that stupid argument
behind us.

12:42.895 --> 12:44.730
This bet was kind of
the best thing

12:44.797 --> 12:46.599
that ever happened
to our friendship.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.503
[ Slow clapping ]

12:50.603 --> 12:51.604
You're welcome.

12:51.670 --> 12:52.805
This great moment
of friendship

12:52.905 --> 12:54.340
has been brought to you
by who?

12:54.440 --> 12:55.841
Miles Alvarez.

12:55.941 --> 12:58.811
So, this was all just a trick
to bring us together?

12:58.911 --> 13:00.312
Yep.
I "Parent Trapped" you.

13:00.412 --> 13:03.315
God, I feel so...duped.

13:03.415 --> 13:04.450
No, you weren't duped.

13:04.517 --> 13:06.085
I manipulated you.

13:06.152 --> 13:07.186
Here -- take these.

13:07.286 --> 13:08.587
You earned 'em.

13:08.654 --> 13:11.490
[ Slow clapping ]

13:11.590 --> 13:12.792
What's going on?

13:12.858 --> 13:13.959
Ha!

13:14.026 --> 13:16.195
We knew you were
"Parent Trapping" us,

13:16.295 --> 13:20.332
so we pretended to get along so
you'd give us our phones back.

13:20.432 --> 13:22.201
Reverse "Parent Trap"!

13:23.602 --> 13:26.972
It took Luke 2 1/2 hours
to explain the movies to me.

13:27.039 --> 13:28.774
We could've just
watched it.

13:30.609 --> 13:32.845
Okay.
How'd you catch on to me?

13:32.945 --> 13:34.380
What do you mean?
It was obvious.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.482
"You two have way more in common
than you think you do."

13:36.549 --> 13:39.552
First of all,
who says that about<i> us?</i>

13:39.652 --> 13:41.787
A normal person
with insight?

13:41.854 --> 13:43.189
Okay.

13:43.289 --> 13:46.192
So, instead of hashing out
our small disagreement,

13:46.292 --> 13:49.128
we spent hours coming up
with this elaborate plan.

13:49.195 --> 13:52.398
Which makes us
the real winners of this bet.

13:52.498 --> 13:53.632
Right.

13:53.699 --> 13:54.900
My two best friends
who never get along

13:55.000 --> 13:57.403
and always put me
in the middle.

13:57.503 --> 13:59.138
You're the real winners.

13:59.205 --> 14:03.242
♪♪

14:03.342 --> 14:04.410
Terrell: Whoa.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.145
That's more than
my summer savings.

14:06.212 --> 14:07.680
This is
with the family discount?

14:07.746 --> 14:10.316
Yeah, my aunts didn't get rich
giving stuff away.

14:11.650 --> 14:14.386
Hey, Sarah, um, did you
have a talk with Terrell yet?

14:14.486 --> 14:18.324
See, I said I'd do it on
my own time, so maybe next week.

14:18.390 --> 14:20.426
Oh, next week's great.
Yeah.

14:20.526 --> 14:21.760
Or today.
Oh, my God, that's a great idea.

14:21.861 --> 14:23.095
Why don't you do it today?

14:23.195 --> 14:24.597
You're not gonna say anything,
right?

14:24.697 --> 14:26.098
No, I promised you
I wouldn't.

14:26.198 --> 14:28.267
Not a word
is gonna leave my lips.

14:28.367 --> 14:30.102
[ School bell rings ]

14:30.202 --> 14:33.205
Okay, class, instead
of our planned debate,

14:33.272 --> 14:35.541
we're actually gonna do
a little communication exercise

14:35.608 --> 14:36.775
I learned at Google.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.111
Does it involve
mining personal data?

14:39.211 --> 14:40.880
Very funny.
[ Chuckles ]

14:40.946 --> 14:42.448
No.

14:42.548 --> 14:46.051
To help make our team stronger,
we are going to be building...

14:46.118 --> 14:48.053
IKEA furniture.

14:48.120 --> 14:49.788
Wait. So you ran home
to get your furniture

14:49.889 --> 14:52.291
because you're too cheap
to hire someone to build it?

14:52.391 --> 14:53.559
No.

14:53.626 --> 14:55.127
I<i> brought in</i> my furniture
to teach you guys

14:55.227 --> 14:56.629
a very important life lesson.

14:56.729 --> 14:58.063
On how to be cheap?

14:58.130 --> 15:00.199
On how to discuss difficult
topics under stress,

15:00.266 --> 15:02.801
which is, I think, something
that we could all work on.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.303
I agree.

15:04.403 --> 15:05.971
I don't.

15:06.071 --> 15:07.740
Perfect example.

15:07.806 --> 15:10.075
So, I'm gonna be choosing teams
of two at random.

15:10.142 --> 15:12.912
It'll be Terrell and...

15:12.978 --> 15:14.880
Mak-- Sarah.

15:14.947 --> 15:15.981
Terrell and Sarah.

15:16.081 --> 15:18.317
Can I see those?

15:18.417 --> 15:20.152
Aww.
Cute couple.

15:20.252 --> 15:21.420
So sweet.

15:21.487 --> 15:23.455
And yet so unnecessary.

15:24.890 --> 15:26.926
And the other teams
are gonna be

15:26.992 --> 15:29.762
Makayla and Robyn
and Luke and Miles.

15:29.828 --> 15:31.897
Great.
There's no instructions.

15:31.964 --> 15:34.667
Maybe the furniture will
trick me into assembling it.

15:34.767 --> 15:36.835
Miles, I know that was
directed towards me.

15:36.936 --> 15:38.137
Oh, my God,
I'm so sorry.

15:38.237 --> 15:40.839
I didn't know
you were right there.

15:40.940 --> 15:43.442
Remember, you two,
communication is key.

15:43.509 --> 15:45.477
And -- And patience, because
building this furniture

15:45.577 --> 15:47.279
could take a long time.

15:47.346 --> 15:48.480
Done.

15:48.580 --> 15:50.683
Really?
You guys had the hardest one.

15:50.783 --> 15:52.484
You're really not getting
the whole

15:52.584 --> 15:55.087
"we're awesome STEM queens"
thing, are you?

15:55.154 --> 15:56.622
Yeah!

15:58.090 --> 15:59.858
Hey, Sarah,
where's the bag of camlocks?

15:59.959 --> 16:01.493
I can't find it.

16:01.593 --> 16:03.796
Oh. Sorry.
I had them here the whole time.

16:03.862 --> 16:06.098
So, is there anything else
you've been withholding, Sarah?

16:06.165 --> 16:08.267
'Cause I'm sure that Terrell
would like to know.

16:08.334 --> 16:09.969
You know, if I think
of anything,

16:10.035 --> 16:12.471
I'm sure I'll pass it on
when I'm ready.

16:12.538 --> 16:14.540
Like now?

16:14.640 --> 16:16.041
[ Both whispering ]

16:16.141 --> 16:18.310
Right. It's just that
this is a partnership.

16:18.377 --> 16:20.045
And so you gotta tell him
what you need

16:20.145 --> 16:21.680
so he doesn't give you
what you don't need.

16:21.780 --> 16:23.649
'Cause you want to build
the strongest armoire possible,

16:23.716 --> 16:25.317
one that will last
well into the future --

16:25.384 --> 16:27.486
Okay. I think
we're moving too fast!

16:30.456 --> 16:31.323
Terrell, what's wrong?

16:31.390 --> 16:32.958
I j-- I need a minute.

16:33.025 --> 16:39.965
♪♪

16:40.032 --> 16:42.634
[<i> Bells chime</i> ]

16:42.701 --> 16:46.739
Luke:<i> This is the</i>
<i>Miles Apology Minute.</i>

16:46.839 --> 16:48.474
An apology?

16:48.540 --> 16:49.975
Okay, I'm listening.

16:50.042 --> 16:51.677
Brought to you by
his two best friends,

16:51.744 --> 16:53.412
who have written a poem.

16:53.512 --> 16:54.546
Please don't read it.

16:54.646 --> 16:57.049
And now we're gonna
read it.

16:57.149 --> 17:00.519
Miles, Miles,
we've had our trials.

17:00.586 --> 17:01.887
Oh, God.

17:01.987 --> 17:03.555
<i>We made you flustered</i>
<i>over our argument</i>

17:03.655 --> 17:04.757
<i>about Dave & Buster's.</i>

17:04.857 --> 17:06.525
No, it keeps getting worse!

17:06.592 --> 17:08.427
Shut your ears,
Ellen Rendecki.

17:09.361 --> 17:12.931
We know you felt like crap
when we revealed...

17:13.031 --> 17:15.834
Both: Our reverse
"Parent Trap."

17:15.901 --> 17:18.504
For the love of Lindsay Lohan,
stop!

17:18.570 --> 17:20.372
Did you hear
the masterpiece?

17:20.439 --> 17:22.040
Everyone in school did.

17:22.107 --> 17:23.675
Well, you'll be pleased
to hear

17:23.742 --> 17:27.079
we wrote it together,
which was your goal.

17:27.179 --> 17:29.381
Yeah. I always sprint
down the hallway in a panic

17:29.448 --> 17:30.783
when I'm pleased.

17:30.883 --> 17:32.951
We just wanted you to know
that we're sorry

17:33.052 --> 17:34.386
for always putting you
in the middle,

17:34.453 --> 17:36.021
and we're gonna do better.

17:36.088 --> 17:39.024
I appreciate that,
but let's get out of here.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.061
It's locked.

17:42.127 --> 17:43.028
Text someone.

17:43.095 --> 17:44.430
I don't have my phone.

17:44.530 --> 17:45.864
Me either.

17:46.765 --> 17:48.067
I got this.

17:48.133 --> 17:51.136
<i>Makayla, this is Miles.</i>
<i>We need your help.</i>

17:51.236 --> 17:52.971
<i>We're locked</i>
<i>in the AV office.</i>

17:53.906 --> 17:55.474
STEM queen to the rescue.

17:55.574 --> 18:01.213
♪♪

18:01.280 --> 18:03.982
Hey, Terrell, I've been
looking for you everywhere.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.218
Y-Yeah, sorry I left you
to do the armoire.

18:06.285 --> 18:07.419
Oh, no, it's okay.

18:07.486 --> 18:09.755
I may have left
a few screws out.

18:09.822 --> 18:12.091
It's a leather jacket away
from collapsing.

18:12.958 --> 18:15.494
I-I didn't mean
to freak out earlier.

18:15.594 --> 18:19.832
I'm just not ready for all
the boyfriend poem stuff.

18:19.932 --> 18:21.667
That's what this is about?

18:21.767 --> 18:22.901
God, no.

18:22.968 --> 18:24.503
Everything got blown
out of proportion.

18:24.603 --> 18:27.406
The -- The poem wasn't
about you, it was about me.

18:27.473 --> 18:29.408
All -- All the swimming
references, though?

18:29.475 --> 18:31.176
Yeah, I swim, too.

18:32.411 --> 18:35.614
<i>I'm</i> the one I wanted to spend
some more time with.

18:35.681 --> 18:38.951
Wow. I mean, you just turned
the EEEEP Award

18:39.017 --> 18:40.519
into a DEEEEP Award.

18:41.620 --> 18:43.622
No, I -- I was so worried
about hurting your feelings,

18:43.689 --> 18:47.526
I didn't know how to tell you,
because I really do like you.

18:47.626 --> 18:49.761
Yeah, yeah,
I like you, too.

18:51.964 --> 18:53.298
But, um...

18:53.365 --> 18:55.868
I think we're better off
as friends.

18:55.968 --> 18:57.136
Oh, thank God.

18:58.770 --> 19:00.038
I feel the same way.

19:00.139 --> 19:01.607
So we're cool?

19:01.673 --> 19:02.774
Yeah.

19:02.841 --> 19:04.143
Always.

19:04.209 --> 19:06.278
Hey, you know, I almost
bought you a bracelet?

19:06.345 --> 19:07.880
There's always
a friendship bracelet.

19:07.980 --> 19:09.681
Not at that price.

19:11.650 --> 19:13.285
I got your text
about that furniture,

19:13.352 --> 19:16.622
and I'm happy to help since
I may have to become a handyman.

19:16.688 --> 19:18.023
You are not getting fired.

19:18.123 --> 19:20.492
And I did it on my own.
I am very resourceful.

19:20.559 --> 19:22.494
Hey, Mr. Escalante.

19:22.561 --> 19:25.864
Sarah, um, again, I --
I am so sorry,

19:25.964 --> 19:27.733
and if it would
make you feel any better,

19:27.833 --> 19:30.202
you could read
my poetry on air.

19:30.302 --> 19:33.405
I definitely
don't want that.

19:33.505 --> 19:34.973
But we're good.

19:35.040 --> 19:36.375
Yeah, things worked out.

19:36.475 --> 19:38.310
Thanks, Ms. G,
for the waxing tip.

19:38.377 --> 19:40.045
Hell yeah.

19:40.145 --> 19:41.580
It's girl stuff.

19:41.680 --> 19:42.915
Men wax, too.

19:44.082 --> 19:47.219
Oh, and here is
your keyboard cord.

19:47.319 --> 19:49.021
[ Chuckles ] Yes!

19:49.087 --> 19:51.757
The Escalante Minute
is back, baby.

19:51.857 --> 19:53.926
Yaaaay.

19:54.026 --> 19:57.029
Thanks for having us
assemble that furniture, Ms. G.

19:58.597 --> 19:59.932
Oh.

20:00.032 --> 20:02.501
Oh, so you did all that
furniture on your own, huh?

20:02.568 --> 20:04.336
I said I was resourceful.

20:04.403 --> 20:05.537
Mm-hmm.

20:05.604 --> 20:07.773
Well, if your furniture's
all done,

20:07.873 --> 20:09.241
guess I'll just head home.

20:09.341 --> 20:11.743
I, uh, still need you to get it
to my apartment.

20:11.843 --> 20:12.945
[ Sighs ]

20:13.045 --> 20:14.780
Fine.
I'll help.

20:14.880 --> 20:18.784
Only if you co-host
the Escalante Minute.

20:18.884 --> 20:20.953
Fine.

20:21.053 --> 20:22.054
But I have
my own theme song.

20:22.120 --> 20:23.689
Ready?
[ Clears throat ]

20:23.755 --> 20:25.290
♪ It's Alicia and Elliot ♪

20:25.390 --> 20:27.960
♪ But mostly Alicia ♪

20:29.561 --> 20:31.029
It's cuter than yours.

20:32.264 --> 20:34.967
♪ That's my best friend,
she a real bad... ♪

20:35.067 --> 20:37.402
♪ Got her own money,
she don't need no... ♪

20:37.469 --> 20:39.972
♪ On the dance floor,
she had two, three drinks ♪

20:40.072 --> 20:42.608
♪ Now she twerkin', she throw it
out and come back in ♪

20:42.708 --> 20:45.210
♪ That's my best friend,
she a real bad... ♪

20:45.277 --> 20:47.713
♪ Drive her own car,
she don't need no Lyft ♪

20:47.779 --> 20:50.215
♪ In the strip club,
know my girl gon' tip ♪

20:50.282 --> 20:53.485
♪ Now she twerkin', she throw it
out and come back in, ha ♪

20:53.585 --> 20:55.654
♪ Best friend, you the baddest
and you know it ♪

20:55.754 --> 20:56.955
♪ You know ♪

20:57.055 --> 20:58.590
♪ I think our booty growin' ♪

20:58.657 --> 21:01.159
♪ ...it up in the mirror,
hit them poses ♪

21:01.260 --> 21:03.095
♪ Best friends,
and you...glowin' ♪

21:03.161 --> 21:04.730
♪ Whoo-whoo! ♪

21:04.796 --> 21:06.331
♪ Look like it's frozen ♪

21:06.431 --> 21:08.300
♪ Uh-oh, girl,
I think our booty growin' ♪

